&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OXFORD CENTRE FOR ENABLEMENT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 6 Neurological Physiotherapist &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;22.5 hours per week. 5 months fixed term contract.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic physiotherapist to join our inpatient neurological rehabilitation team at the Oxford Centre for Enablement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Oxford Centre for Enablement (OCE) is a level one specialist neurological rehabilitation centre providing assessment, management and treatment for patients with a wide range of neurological disorders. This post will be based in our inpatient service. The role will involve working as part of a multidisciplinary team to deliver high quality, patient-centred rehabilitation. There will be opportunities to develop skills in specialist areas such as spasticity management, splinting, electrical stimulation and hydrotherapy.This is a very supportive clinical environment and the post holder can expect to develop their knowledge and skills within a well-established and experienced team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are strongly encouraged to discuss the post in advance of applying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planned interview date: to be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
